What Is a â€œPrivate Folderâ€ in Next.js?
      A private folder is any folder whose name starts with an underscore (_),
    like this:
    
    app/
     â””â”€â”€ blog/
          â”œâ”€â”€ _components/
          â””â”€â”€ page.js
    
    
    ğŸ‘‰ Next.js treats folders starting with _ as non-routable â€”
    they are ignored by the routing system.

