What is Metadata in Next.js:
      In the App Router, metadata is a built-in SEO system that automatically updates <head> tags for every route â€” including titles, descriptions, Open Graph tags, favicons, etc.
      No need to manually use <Head> anymore.

    Two Ways to Define Metadata

        You can define metadata in:
              Static object export
              Dynamic function export
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

What is the Link Component:
    In Next.js, the Link component (from next/link) enables client-side navigation â€” meaning fast page transitions without full reloads.
____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Navigating Programmatically:
    â€œNavigating programmaticallyâ€ means changing the current page or route using code instead of a user manually clicking a link or button.

      "use client";
import { useRouter } from "next/navigation";

export default function Page() {
  const router = useRouter();

  const goToHome = () => {
    router.push("/home");
  };

  return <button onClick={goToHome}>Go Home</button>;
}
____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Templates:
      Templates are similar to layouts, but with one big difference:
Templates re-render from scratch every time you navigate between pages that share them.

| Feature                           | Layout                                | Template                                                             |
| --------------------------------- | ------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Shared between routes             | âœ… Yes                                 | âœ… Yes                                                                |
| Preserves state on navigation     | âœ… Yes                                 | âŒ No                                                                 |
| Recreates DOM elements            | âŒ No                                  | âœ… Yes                                                                |
| Re-runs effects (useEffect, etc.) | âŒ No                                  | âœ… Yes                                                                |
| Use case                          | Persistent UI (navbar, sidebar, etc.) | Pages that need reset state per navigation (forms, animations, etc.) |

